# Frontend Development Guidelines

## Nuxt 3 Best Practices

### Component Organization
- Use Composition API with `<script setup>`
- Keep components small and focused
- Extract reusable logic to composables
- Follow component naming conventions:
  - PascalCase for component names
  - kebab-case for filenames

### TypeScript Usage
- Enable strict type checking
- Avoid `any` type usage
- Define proper interfaces and types
- Use type inference when possible
- Reference [useLocalization.ts](mdc:apps/frontend/src/composables/useLocalization.ts) for type examples

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Extract common styles to `@styles` directory
- Follow mobile-first approach
- Use proper responsive design patterns

### Internationalization
- Use `useLocalization` composable for translations
- Store translations in `i18n/locales/*.json`
- Follow translation key structure
- Avoid hardcoded strings

### State Management
- Use composables for local state
- Extract complex logic from components
- Follow reactive patterns
- Use proper TypeScript types

### Performance
- Implement proper SSR strategies
- Use lazy loading when appropriate
- Optimize image loading
- Follow Nuxt 3 best practices

### Code Quality
- Keep functions small and focused
- Use early returns
- Implement proper error handling
- Follow SOLID principles where applicable

### Component Guidelines
- Prefer functional components
- Use proper prop validation
- Implement proper event handling
- Follow Vue 3 lifecycle hooks

### SEO Optimization
- Use proper meta tags
- Implement SSR for important content
- Follow accessibility guidelines
- Use semantic HTML

### Testing
- Write unit tests for components
- Test composables thoroughly
- Use Vue Test Utils
- Follow testing best practices

## Common Components
Reuse existing components for:
- Pagination
- Sliders
- Filters
- Cards
- Form elements
- Modal dialogs

## Error Handling
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use try-catch blocks appropriately
- Show user-friendly error messages
- Log errors properly
